Description: The Quantitative Variable Distribution module, part of the larger 
    SQUBA ecosystem, evaluates the distribution of quantitative variables and/or the 
    distribution of patient counts for variables within a study cohort. This allows 
    investigators to ensure that the distribution of values for a given variable, 
    like dosages for a drug, align with clinical expectations. Users can also 
    evaluate the spread of patient counts for a given variable, like the number of 
    patients with an inpatient visit, to ensure that utilization 
    patterns align with expectations.
